newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ futures settle lower, under key support.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ futures settle lower, under key support.

text.p: FCOJ futures continued to back away from recent gains and closed under the 20-day moving average, where analysts had pegged key support basis the March contract.
The spot month settled down 2.25 at 84.15 cents, below support pegged at 84.35 cents. The deferred contracts ended 2.30 lower to 0.20 higher.
Analysts said today's close sets the stage for additional losses. Major support in March was seen below the contract low of 76.40 cents, at 75.00 cents.
The lingering uncertainty surrounding losses from the Jan 19 freeze has put trade selling on hold, market sources said.
"A lot of people in the trade will stand aside until the report comes out," an analyst said.
The U.S. Department of Agriculture will release its estimate for the 1996/97 Florida crop Feb 12.

Meanwhile, the near-term weather outlook calls for mild temperatures through the middle of next week. Although there is a potential for freezing weather by the end of next week, forecasters said it is too soon to predict how low temperatures could fall.
"It will get cooler but it is too early to pinpoint temperatures," Mike Palmerino of Weather Services Corp, said.
